      "author": "github-actions[bot]",
      "description": "## Batch now does summarize → title → tag\n\nThe folder batch (**Summarize link notes in folder**) now enriches each link-only note in one pass:\n\n- **Title** — the note is renamed to a concise, AI-generated title derived from its summary (name collisions are resolved automatically).\n- **Tags** — 2–4 lowercase topic tags are merged into frontmatter (existing tags are preserved, not replaced).\n- **Best-effort** — if the title/tag step fails, the summary still lands and the note still counts as done.\n- New **Generate title and tags** setting (default on) under a *Batch* section — turn it off for summary-only runs.\n\nImplementation reuses the existing (debugged) summary pipeline via an extracted `runProviderCompletion` helper and the generic rate-limit retry, so the title/tag call also waits out per-minute 429s. Note: this adds a second provider call per note, so it roughly halves how many notes you can process against a daily quota.",
      "downloadCount": 1,
