      "author": "github-actions[bot]",
      "description": "First tagged release since 0.3.2 — includes everything from 0.5.0–0.5.2.\n\n## Auth-gated pages via a logged-in browser session (0.5.0)\n- **Browser fetch** mode renders a page in a persistent, logged-in Electron `<webview>`, so auth-gated links (LinkedIn, X, Telegram, …) can be summarized where a plain provider fetch hits a login wall.\n- Command **“Log in to sites for browser fetch”** — sign in once; the session persists across summaries.\n- New **Fetch mode** setting (Auto / Provider-native / Browser) and a configurable **auth-gated hosts** list.\n\n## Batch-summarize a folder (0.5.1)\n- Folder context-menu item **“Summarize link notes in folder”** and command **“Summarize link notes in current folder”**.\n- Finds link-only notes (a bare URL, not yet summarized), shows a confirmation with the count, then summarizes each in place as a `> [!summary]` callout.\n- Idempotent (skips already-summarized notes), with live progress and a done/failed tally; honors the private-network guard and API-key check.\n\n## Model defaults (0.5.2)\n- Default models updated to Gemini 3.5 Flash and GPT-5.5 Instant.\n\n**Note:** browser fetch and login are desktop-only.",
